defs.docs:
This crate is a port of
 [Haskell's QuickCheck](http://hackage.haskell.org/package/QuickCheck).

defs.name: Gen
defs.docs:
`Gen` wraps a `rand::RngCore` with parameters to control the distribution of
 random values.

defs.name: StdGen
defs.docs: StdGen is the default implementation of `Gen`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Returns a `StdGen` with the given configuration using any random number
 generator.

defs.name: StdThreadGen
defs.docs: StdThreadGen is an RNG in thread-local memory.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Returns a new thread-local RNG.

defs.name: empty_shrinker
defs.docs: Creates a shrinker with zero elements.

defs.name: single_shrinker
defs.docs: Creates a shrinker with a single element.

defs.name: Arbitrary
defs.docs:
`Arbitrary` describes types whose values can be randomly generated and
 shrunk.

defs.name: QuickCheck
defs.docs: The main QuickCheck type for setting configuration and running QuickCheck.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new QuickCheck value.

defs.name: tests
defs.docs: Set the number of tests to run.

defs.name: with_gen
defs.docs: Create a new instance of `QuickCheck` using the given generator.

defs.name: max_tests
defs.docs: Set the maximum number of tests to run.

defs.name: gen
defs.docs: Set the random number generator to be used by QuickCheck.

defs.name: min_tests_passed
defs.docs: Set the minimum number of tests that needs to pass.

defs.name: quicktest
defs.value: fn <A> (&mut self, f: A) -> Result<u64, TestResult>
defs.docs: Tests a property and returns the result.

defs.name: quickcheck
defs.docs: Tests a property and calls `panic!` on failure.

defs.name: quickcheck
defs.docs: Convenience function for running QuickCheck.

defs.name: TestResult
defs.docs: Describes the status of a single instance of a test.

defs.name: passed
defs.docs: Produces a test result that indicates the current test has passed.

defs.name: failed
defs.docs: Produces a test result that indicates the current test has failed.

defs.name: error
defs.docs: Produces a test result that indicates failure from a runtime error.

defs.name: discard
defs.docs:
Produces a test result that instructs `quickcheck` to ignore it.
 This is useful for restricting the domain of your properties.
 When a test is discarded, `quickcheck` will replace it with a
 fresh one (up to a certain limit).

defs.name: from_bool
defs.docs:
Converts a `bool` to a `TestResult`. A `true` value indicates that
 the test has passed and a `false` value indicates that the test
 has failed.

defs.name: must_fail
defs.docs:
Tests if a "procedure" fails when executed. The test passes only if
 `f` generates a task failure during its execution.

defs.name: is_failure
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if and only if this test result describes a failing
 test.

defs.name: is_error
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if and only if this test result describes a failing
 test as a result of a run time error.

defs.name: Testable
defs.docs:
`Testable` describes types (e.g., a function) whose values can be
 tested.
